{
  "texts": [
    "(compare (Gronauer & Diepold, 2021)) PPO (IPPO) can outperform state-of-the-art joint learning approaches on popular multi-agent benchmarks.",
    "Yu et al. (2021) investigate Multi-Agent PPO, a variant of PPO specialized for multi-agent settings.",
    "They show that Multi-Agent PPO achieves surprisingly strong performance in multiagent benchmarks, with minimal hyperparameter tuning and without any domain-specific algorithmic modifications or architectures.",
    "In most environments, they show that Multi-Agent PPO achieves strong results compared to off-policy baselines while exhibiting comparable sample efficiency.",
    "To solve the layout and scheduling problem in LMAS, an algorithm tackling the integrated DFLP and FJSP is needed."
  ]
}